        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 5:07PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
and just west of Etna, or 28 miles southwest of Yreka. This storm
was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Siskiyou
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
